<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-5377] pDAcroForm.flatten() does not remove /SigFlags in /Catalog object</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-5377</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A PDF document contains Signature fields (X.509) with /SigFlags 1 indication in the /Catalog object.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When the document is flattened, this signature image remains in the document and underlying object is removed. Perfect!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But the SigFlags in /Catalog object is not removed although this has no value anymore and prevent the document being correct signed/certifiied afterwards (at least with our software).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can the SigFlags in /Catalog object be removed or its value be changed to 0 so this corresponds to the content of the document ?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
